From c06505cf4145a61bc9b8189b7170ed792345d55d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: SlayZone Dev <dev@slayzone.local>
Date: Sun, 19 Apr 2026 18:35:32 +0200
Subject: [slayzone] slayzone: Phase 7.1 statusbar webui +
 SlayzoneStatusbarHost

First real SlayZone surface in the fork. Adds:

- chrome/browser/slayzone/mojom/statusbar.mojom: StatusbarHost with a
  single GetSnapshot() => (StatusbarSnapshot) method. Mirror of the
  outer packages/shared/mojo-bindings/mojom/statusbar.mojom; the two
  stay diff-identical below the module line.
- slayzone_statusbar_host.{h,cc}: per-SlayzoneBrowserView Mojo impl.
  GetSnapshot forwards to SidecarClient::Call(statusbar:get-snapshot).
  Sidecar response dict -> StatusbarSnapshot struct; empty response
  (disconnected) yields a sensible disconnected frame.
- chrome/browser/ui/webui/slayzone/slayzone_statusbar_ui.{h,cc}:
  chrome://slayzone-statusbar/ WebUIController. Serves the
  @slayzone/webui-statusbar Vite bundle from
  --slayzone-webui-bundle-dir/<region>/dist/ (inline error page when
  the flag is missing). CSP override allows script-src 'self'
  chrome://resources + style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' for the hashed
  Vite assets plus the Chromium Mojo JS runtime. BindInterface mirrors
  the Phase 6.3 pattern (FromRegionWebContents ->
  view->statusbar_host()->Bind).
- SlayzoneBrowserView: owns a SlayzoneStatusbarHost; new
  statusbar_host() accessor.
- SlayzoneRegionContainer::RegionUrl: routes 'statusbar' region to the
  dedicated host (replaces the placeholder URL).
- ChromeURLHosts()/webui_url_constants: register
  chrome://slayzone-statusbar/ host.
- chrome_browser_interface_binders_webui_parts_desktop: registers
  ForWebUI<SlayzoneStatusbarUI>().Add<StatusbarHost>().
- BUILD.gn: new .cc/.h files wired into browser + ui targets;
  mojom/BUILD.gn adds statusbar.mojom.
- sidecar_client.cc: swap LSP (Content-Length) framing for NDJSON.
  Cross-phase fix surfaced by Phase 7.1 verification: the Phase 2.3
  C++ shim encoded outgoing messages with Content-Length headers but
  the Phase 3.4 sidecar server (packages/sidecar/src/server/framing.ts)
  decodes NDJSON. Socket connection established silently but no RPC
  ever flowed. NDJSON is the single source of truth (chosen in 3.4 for
  debuggability); patching the C++ shim to match is the smallest fix.
